12 SIMDs activated in March. The big one is P-Token, a drop-in replacement for SPL that cuts transfer compute from ~4,645 CU to ~76 CU, freeing ~12% of block space (live on devnet). 

@anza_xyz also published Constellation, proposing 16 concurrent proposers in 50ms slots to enforce censorship resistance by removing transaction ordering from any single validator. 

And @DoubleZero Edge now connects ~28% of total Solana stake across 444 validators, with Phase II dropping fees to zero and redistributing 2.4M SOL to validators in underrepresented regions.

